Edition:
Quote:  [fn]Haka was a general term for the dance and a perfectly peacable, welcoming and fraternal haka might bear all the marks - to the uninitiated - of extreme fury and blood thirstiness. The war-dance was  properly called peruperu and was a really formidable exhibition
